{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, the generalization gap diminishes.",
    "It is worth noting that a decrease in training accuracy is also observed for the true labeling of data 54.Corrupted labels.",
    "Next to the randomization of labels, we further investigate the QCNN fitting behavior when data come with varying levels of label corruption D r, ranging from no labels being altered (r = 0) to all of them being corrupted (r = 1).",
    "The experiments consider different number of training points N ∈ {4, 6, 8}, and a fixed number of qubits n = 8.",
    "For each combination of (n, N), we start the experiments with no randomized labels (r = 0)."
  ]
}